KW  - regression adjustment
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA20289
Y2  - 2024/10/27
N2  - Freedman (2008a,b) showed that the linear regression estimator is biased for the analysis of randomized controlled trials under the randomization model. Under Freedman's assumptions, we derive exact closed-form bias corrections for the linear regression estimator. We show that the limiting distribution of the bias corrected estimator is identical to the uncorrected estimator. Taken together with results from Lin (2013), our results show that Freedman's theoretical arguments against the use of regression adjustment can be resolved with minor modifications to practice.
ER  - 

TY  - JOUR
T1  - Robust Real Rate Rules
AU  - Holden, Tom D.
Y1  - 2024/09/01
PY  - 2024
